President Biden has announced that Stephen Benjamin will be the Senior Advisor and Director of the Office of Public Engagement. In this role, Benjamin will oversee the White House Office of Public Engagement, which works to ensure that community leaders, diverse perspectives, and new voices have the opportunity to inform the work of the President in an inclusive and responsible way. Benjamin is a former Mayor of Columbia, South Carolina, and has served as President of both the U.S. Conference of Mayors and the African American Mayors Association. He has a strong background in economic development, job creation, and law enforcement. Benjamin will be taking over from Keisha Lance Bottoms, who has served as the Director of the Office of Public Engagement and will be returning home to Atlanta.